did.abstract: The History of Education Society was founded in 1960 and works to promote the study of the history of education by scholars and by people who work for education policy and reform. The records in this collection tell the story of this organization through meeting minutes, financial records, conference programs, committee and Board of Trustees rosters, images, correspondence, the records of the History of Education Quarterly the HES journal. The records cover the founding in 1960 through 2013.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Within the records of the initial donation March 2015 and subsequent donation from October 2020 the "accepted and rejected manuscripts" submitted to the History of Education Quarterly are restricted from use for 50 years from date of donation. This is to protect the privacy of authors and peer reviewers.

All donations from HES to GW starting in May 2021, will arrive at GW with any personally identifiable information redacted. These redacted records will be available without restriction for use by the public following archival processing.

At the end of their tenure editing the History of Education Quarterly the editorial team will donate a spreadsheet that provides the list of authors, reviewers, manuscript titles, and manuscript numbers. Each spreadsheet will be restricted from use for 50 years from the date of donation.

bioghist.head: Organizational history
bioghist.p: In 1948, the National Society of College Teachers of Education began a History of Education Section. The Section published the History of Education Journal. Throughout the 1950s, scholars argued over the field's aims and in 1960 the History of Education Society was founded as an independent organization, succeeding the Section. The society influenced by revisionism in the 1970s encouraged its historians to debate American public education's societal and individual roles in the society's journal and annual meetings. In 1961, the History of Education Quarterly replaced the History of Education Journal and published the society's work. The journal operated out of the University of Pittsburgh, later moved to New York University, and has subsequently been affiliated with Indiana University, Slippery Rock University, the University of Illinois and the University of Washington. In 1988, the society affiliated with the International Standing Conference for the History of Education, which hosts annual meetings for the field around the world in conjunction with regional history of education societies. The History of Education Society holds an annual conference in October, in addition, the Society also hosts several awards for scholars. From its Website From its Website the HES describes its goals as: promoting and improving the teaching of the history of education in colleges and universities, encouraging scholarly research in the history of education and facilitating the publication and dissemination of the results of this research, working to interest education professionals and the public in the value of the historical perspective when making education policy, promoting libraries and museums to preserve source materials used in the study of the history of education, encouraging the collaboration of scholars throughout the world on studies and the exchange of documents and ideas and cooperating with organizations of professional historians and professional educators throughout the world.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains meeting minutes, financial records, conference programs, reports, committee rosters, Board of Director rosters, correspondence and photographs related to the history of the organization. The material dates from 1960 through 2013.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection is not fully processed. Specifically, series 4 is unprocessed at this time.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Within the records of the initial donation March 2015 the "accepted and rejected manuscripts" submitted to the History of Education Quarterly are restricted from use for 50 years from date of donation. This is to protect the privacy of authors and peer reviewers. Future donations that have content governed by the addendum to the deed of gift will not be added to the collection management system prior to the end of the restriction and therefore not be described in this series.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains accepted and rejected manuscript submissions that contain personally identifiable information.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series contains one subseries. This arrangement allows GW to make public that this series exists while suppressing the records that within the folder titles may contain restricted information. This arrangement will allow GW to close there records, but retain the descriptive metadata and make it easier to open to users when the restriction ends.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The collection materials within this series are restricted from use for use for 50 years from date of donation. This content was originally part of series 4 Journal - History of Education Quarterly and when the restriction ends in 2065 these records will return to series 3. Therefore the unique component identifer for the File level records still read Series 3.
